Commentary Text: Shami to Rohit, out Caught by Neesham!! Tag-team effort by Maxwell and Neesham has helped Punjab get rid of the Hitman. Maxwell did all the hard work there, but Neesham makes sure that his effort isn't in vain. Was lofted towards long-off by Rohit as Maxy grabbed it and just when he was about to overhaul the boundary, he parried it to Neesham who was charging across from long-on. Commentary Text: Gowtham to Ishan Kishan, out Caught by Nair!! Ishan Kishan's struggle comes to an end. Probably, a blessing in disguise for Mumbai Indians. Time for Pollard and the Pandya brothers to take charge from here on. Was down on his knee to play the slogsweep as Kishan finds the man at deep mid-wicket. Two contrasting knocks for Kishan then. 99 the other night, and only 28 tonight. More importantly, he has used up too many deliveries in this innings. Ishan Kishan c Nair b Gowtham 28(32) [4s-1 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Pattinson to Pooran, out Caught by de Kock!! A game of angles, nothing else folks. You would think how on earth did a set batsman of Pooran's ability not muscle that juicy full ball over the ropes. but there's a lot on the technical side in this game. Pooran took the invitation without knowing there was trap, he swung too hard and lost a bit of shape which is why he couldn't find the middle. Edge to QdK who takes a simple catch. A lot of times people wonder why Cottrell and not Jordan in a team. It's all about the angles. Left-arm angle to right-handeed batsman isn't all that easy. Pooran c de Kock b Pattinson 44(27) [4s-3 6s-2]

Commentary Text: Bumrah to Agarwal, out Bowled!! Castled! Massive breakthrough as Bumrah goes right through a dangerous Agarwal. Pitched right up, finds movement off the seam as it comes in off the deck. Agarwal hadn't bargained for it. He threw his hands on the drive without any footwork. It's a shot you play on a flat pitch. This, however, has something in it. Bowls him through the gate. Agarwal b Bumrah 25(18) [4s-3]
